title: [KYLIN-4068] append limit and offset to sql reliably
body:
## What changes were proposed in this pull request?
Currently, there is a bug in sql conversion, as follow:

```sql
SELECT E_Name FROM Employees_China
UNION
SELECT E_Name FROM Employees_USA
```

will convert to

```sql
SELECT E_Name FROM Employees_China
UNION
SELECT E_Name FROM Employees_USA
LIMIT 50000
```

This limit is not working on the result of union, but on SELECT E_Name FROM Employees_USA.
We should use a more secure way to achieve the limit effect.

This pr fixed the bug, making sure to append limit or offset after sql does not change sql semantics

body:
Currently, the function of ingest data from RDBMS(kylin.source.default=8) to Kylin has some problems , in this patch, I want to fix:

- fix case-sensitive
- fix weak dialect compatibility
- fix mis-use quote character


Manually test passed under 
- MySQL 5.7
- SqlServer 2017

IT test passed


### Configuration

- Sql Server 2017
```
kylin.source.default=8
kylin.source.jdbc.connection-url=jdbc:sqlserver://hdp30-qa:1433;DatabaseName=DemoData
kylin.source.jdbc.driver=com.microsoft.sqlserver.jdbc.SQLServerDriver
kylin.source.jdbc.dialect=mssql
kylin.source.jdbc.user=sa
kylin.source.jdbc.pass=SqlServer_2017
kylin.source.jdbc.filed-delimiter=|
kylin.source.jdbc.sqoop-home=/usr/hdp/current/sqoop-client
```

- MySQL 5.7

```
kylin.source.jdbc.driver=com.mysql.jdbc.Driver
kylin.source.jdbc.dialect=mysql
kylin.source.jdbc.user=root
kylin.source.jdbc.pass=MysqlTest_57
kylin.source.jdbc.filed-delimiter=|
kylin.source.jdbc.sqoop-home=/usr/hdp/current/sqoop-client
```

### Model

```sql

SELECT `USERACTION`.`USER_ID` as `USERACTION_USER_ID` ,
 `USERACTION`.`ACT_TYPE` as `USERACTION_ACT_TYPE` ,
 `USERACTION`.`ITEM_ID` as `USERACTION_ITEM_ID` ,
 `USERACTION`.`LOG_TIME` as `USERACTION_LOG_TIME` ,
 `VIDEOINFO`.`VIDEO_ID` as `VIDEOINFO_VIDEO_ID` ,
 `VIDEOINFO`.`VIDEO_TYPE` as `VIDEOINFO_VIDEO_TYPE` ,
 `VIDEOINFO`.`VIDEO_DURATION` as `VIDEOINFO_VIDEO_DURATION` ,
 `WHERE`.`VIDEO_ID` as `WHERE_VIDEO_ID` ,
 `WHERE`.`SELECT` as `WHERE_SELECT` ,
 `WHERE`.`VIDEO_DURATION` as `WHERE_VIDEO_DURATION` ,
 `USERACTION`.`ACTIVE_MINUTES` as `USERACTION_ACTIVE_MINUTES` ,
 `USERACTION`.`PLAY_TIMES` as `USERACTION_PLAY_TIMES` ,
 `USERACTION`.`PV_ID` as `USERACTION_PV_ID`  
FROM `DBO`.`USERACTION` as `USERACTION` 
  LEFT JOIN `DBO`.`VIDEOINFO` as `VIDEOINFO` ON `USERACTION`.`ITEM_ID` = `VIDEOINFO`.`VIDEO_ID` 
  LEFT JOIN `DBO`.`WHERE` as `WHERE` ON `VIDEOINFO`.`VIDEO_TYPE` = `WHERE`.`SELECT` WHERE 1=1
--
```

title: KYLIN-4047 Use push-down query when division dynamic column cube query is not supported
body:
Scene：

SQL:select round (car_dismatch_cnt*100/answer_order_cnt, 4) from db.table1.

- 1、Executes the SQL on a  project where its cube has db.table1,it will throws the right side of the BinaryTuple Expressions columns is not supported for / exception and is not queried through pushdown;

- 2、When change a project where not create the table cube , the same query  can be executed to push down and get the right result.

- 3、 Expect that no matter whether a table cube is created or not, when the cube query is not success, the result can still be obtained by pushdown query, which will give users a consistent experience.

```
【Design】：Setting the cache for curator is never invalid (unless the service stops) and check the state before use curator instance (if closed ,create a new curator instance and put into the cache)
```
